[Patient] What kind of exercise can I do to help my heart failure?
[Educator] Walking in your safe neighborhood or following online workout videos can be beneficial.
[Patient] I don't have money for a gym membership. What should I do?
[Educator] Look for free exercise classes in the community or ask a friend to exercise with you.
[Patient] I'm worried about safety while walking in my neighborhood. Any suggestions?
[Educator] Try walking during daylight hours with a friend or family member for added safety.
[Patient] How often should I exercise to help with my heart failure?
[Educator] Aim for at least 30 minutes of moderate exercise most days of the week for heart health.
[Patient] I struggle with motivation to exercise. Any tips to stay on track?
[Educator] Set achievable goals, track your progress, and find a workout buddy for support and motivation.